  "prompt": "When travelling by plane, is your luggage full?",
  "response": "When traveling by plane, whether your luggage is full or not depends on your personal packing habits and the length of your trip. Some travelers might pack their luggage to the brim, especially for longer vacations, while others may prefer to pack lightly, leaving extra space for souvenirs or shopping. Additionally, factors like the airline's baggage policy, the duration of the trip, and personal preferences for clothing and items can influence how full one's luggage is.",
